         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Lund 11 September 1882. ¶ Highly esteemed Baron! ¶  ¶ I suspect that you have long ago received my letter ¶  with the name determinations of algae that were collected by  ¶ Spong ¶  in King Island, ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">82.09.11a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M108a, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M 'Beantw [Answered] 18/1/83 F.v.M.' Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Lund 11 Sept. 1882.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochgeehrter Herr Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich vermuthe dass Sie meinen Brief mit Nahmen bestimmung der Algen, welche von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Spong</hi>
               </seg> in Kings Island, von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ramsay</hi>
               </seg> at Port Jackson, und von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Tepper</hi>
               </seg> at Vincents Gulf gesammelt waren, schon längst erhalten haben. Gleichzeitig habe ich an die Frau Doctorin Sonder geschrieben wegen Uebersendung der Algen, aber Sie war damals auf eine Reise in Mecklenburg, und erst in einem Brief von 31 Juli habe ich Ihr Antwort erhalten. Sie erklärt darin, dass es Ihr erfreuen werde, wenn Ich die Bearbeitung der Algen übernehmen sollte. So bald Sie nach Hamburg zurück käme, wurde Sie die Algen samlungen mir übersenden lassen. Späther habe ich nichts davon gehört. In den letzten 2 remissen von 11/7 und 17/7 ist nur eine Form neu; diese ist aber von intresse als eine von den früher bekanten Arten von Melanthalia, welche sich gegenseitig sehr näheren, gut geschiedene Species. Von den übrigen, die beynahe alle den allgemeinsten australischen Arten zugehören, habe ich einige fragmente, oder wo mehrere Exemplare vorräthig waren, das eine zurückbehalten.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochachtend zeichnet</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J G Agardh</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">1. List of Algae from Fowlers bay<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">SA.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> near Gr. Bight from Mrs Richards.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Specimens 1 &amp; 2. <name key="Ptilocladia%20pulchra">Ptilocladia pulchra</name> Sond.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">3 &amp; 4. <name key="Callophyllis%20Lambertii">Callophyllis Lambertii</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">5 &amp; 6. <name key="Callophyllis%20coccinea">Callophyllis coccinea</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">7-9 <name key="Plocamium%20nidificum">Plocamium nidificum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">10-12 <name key="Hypnea%20episcopalis">Hypnea episcopalis</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">13. <name key="Hymenocladia%20divaricata">Hymenocladia divaricata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">14. <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name> var. <seg>β </seg>J. Ag. Epicr.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Agardh (1848-1901), vol. 3, part 1, p. 546.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">15 Dictymenia tridens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">16. <name key="Hennedya%20crispa">Hennedya crispa</name> Harv.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">17 Rhodophyllis nitophylloides Harv.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">18 <name key="Delesseria%20coriifolia">Delesseria coriifolia</name> Harv.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">19. <name key="Delesseria%20denticulata">Delesseria denticulata</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">20. Conferva near to C. Bainesii Harv.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Conferva bainesii</seg> not in AlgaeBase; the ony <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. bainseii</seg> listed is <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cladophera bainseii</seg> (accessed 1 August 2016).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">List of Algae from coast near Mt Dromedary<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> by Miss Bate.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mary Bate.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">No. 1. <name key="Plocamium%20procerum">Plocamium procerum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">2. no alga — species of Sertularia</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">3. <name key="Cystophora%20paniculata">Cystophora paniculata</name> with a Sertularia</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">4a. <name key="Phacelocarpus%20alatus">Phacelocarpus alatus</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">4b. <name key="Phacelocarpus%20apodus">Phacelocarpus apodus</name>? (but not in fruit)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">5 <name key="Sphacelaria%20paniculata">Sphacelaria paniculata</name> Suhr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">6. (no specimen present)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">7. <name key="Melanthalia%20obtusata%20intermedia">Melanthalia obtusata intermedia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">8. <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">9. <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">10. <name key="Gelidium%20australe">Gelidium australe</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">11. <name key="Phacelocarpus%20Labillardieri">Phacelocarpus Labillardieri</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">12. perhaps <name key="Griffithsia%20antarctica">Griffithsia antarctica</name> (no fruit present)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">13. <name key="Callophyllis%20coccinea">Callophyllis coccinea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">14. no alga — is a Flustra</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">15. <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">16. <name key="Melanthalia%20polydactylis">Melanthalia polydactylis</name> J. Ag. nov. sp.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Type specimen is in MEL.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">17a. <name key="Plocamium%20costatum">Plocamium costatum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">17b. <name key="Plocamium%20angustum">Plocamium angustum</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">18. no Alga — perhaps a Bryozoon.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
