            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">20 <name key="Microthoe%20marginata">Microthoe marginata</name> Harv. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">21 no specimen present.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">22. <name key="Areschougia%20Stuartii">Areschougia Stuartii</name> Harv.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Lund 11 September 1882.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Highly esteemed Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I suspect that you have long ago received my letter<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found, but see M to. E. Ramsay, 22 September 1882 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>82-09-22c).</p>
               </note> with the name determinations of algae that were collected by <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Spong</hi>
               </seg> in King Island,<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Tas.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> from <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ramsay</hi>
               </seg> at Port Jackson<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sydney Harbour.</p>
               </note> and from <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Tepper</hi>
               </seg> at Vincents Gulf.<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">St Vincent’s Gulf, SA.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> At the same time I have written to Mrs Sonder on sending the algae, but she was at that time on a journey in Mecklenburg and I received her answer only in a letter of 31 July. She says that she will be pleased if I should take over the working up of the algae. As soon as she comes back to Hamburg, she will have the algae collection sent to me. Later I have heard nothing of it. In the last two sendings of 11 July and 17 July only one form is new; but this is of interest as one of the previously known species of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Melanthalia</seg>, which very much brings together well separated species. Of the remainder, which belong to nearly all the most common Australian species, I have retained some fragments or one specimen where several were available.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Very respectfully subscribes</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. G. Agardh</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
